"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"7350fa5dd6ef073aa160d126ed4ca276d234dbce657bb21089fa1797d1266f25","event_uuid":"cec5f840-0b6b-416a-ae27-51d122a6e230","position":{"commit_sha":"b4520a6167dd58b1904a24f08456b56533459225","position":"1784264925388069001-cec5f840-0b6b-416a-ae27-51d122a6e230"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"cd26b309957c9a3bddb27c7a11b663b797b1eece5d609a0ad7dc7990099b7a82","event_uuid":"8a701a8e-a0a6-4b2f-8b3c-a3a171b500a6","position":{"commit_sha":"bdb0f3c37e15ac8f00f6ebdbce10d3eb24cedd83","position":"1784264928125987001-8a701a8e-a0a6-4b2f-8b3c-a3a171b500a6"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"d08943810e70251b6974c1fa55354bc3544edb7a50dc929f552e7a2cb49635cf","event_uuid":"5f5de3af-73a0-4387-a030-8f7221fbef02","position":{"commit_sha":"62fba2282ea1d14cb4381123e1f74747f22d58f4","position":"1784264946515813001-5f5de3af-73a0-4387-a030-8f7221fbef02"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"aa9cb5ff-3fdb-44d3-8af8-c125c27f20ad","comments":[],"created_at":1784230954088867001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"5f7861a5-9ff1-4569-8f14-4c7691f22952","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"}],"description":"# Create canonical AGENTS.md (rebar dev guide) + reduce CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md pointer\n\n## Why\n\n`AGENTS.md` is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp,\nFactory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline — so one canonical `AGENTS.md` covers the ecosystem,\nand Claude Code is bridged by a one-line import. This also fixes the size/duplication\nanti-pattern: sections that duplicate a `docs/` file become one-line pointers.\n\n## What\n\nAuthor a lean `AGENTS.md` at the repo root that keeps rebar-INTERNAL developer specifics inline\nand replaces every already-documented topic with a one-line `docs/…md` pointer. Then reduce\n`CLAUDE.md` to a single `@AGENTS.md` import plus an optional `## Claude Code` section.\n\n- **INLINE (kept in full):** intro; the record-work/claim-before-you-work operating rules; the\n  parallel-agent loop; env bootstrap (`make install`/`make hooks`); module-size policy; Serena\n  navigation; a **condensed** Git/Gerrit section; a 6-line library snippet.\n- **POINTER (one line each), to EXISTING docs:** gate protocols → `docs/plan-review-gate.md`;\n  quality gates + ticket template + project criteria → `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md`; MCP\n  tool set → `docs/mcp-reference.md`; store-shares-writes + parent-first cascade →\n  `docs/concurrency.md`; ticket model → `docs/ticket-model.md` (created by S1); session logs →\n  `docs/event-schema.md` + `docs/user-guide.md`; library reference → `docs/reuse-surface.md`; the\n  LLM agent-operations topic → `docs/llm-framework.md`; the completion close-gate →\n  `docs/plan-review-gate.md`. These are POINTERS only — this story writes no content into those\n  docs (their content already exists; the two \"stowaway\" topics currently mixed into CLAUDE.md's\n  Session-logs heading are simply not carried into AGENTS.md).\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: new `AGENTS.md`, rewritten `CLAUDE.md`. No writes to any `docs/*` file (pointers only). Out:\n`CLAUDE.local.md` (S3), the shim/reference sweep (S6), and code. **Depends on S1** (already linked\n`depends_on`): `docs/ticket-model.md` must exist before `AGENTS.md` points at it. Rollback is a\nplain `git revert` (docs/text only).\n\n## Design decisions (spike-validated)\n\n- The `@AGENTS.md` import is PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211 (headless canary + official docs\n  recommend exactly `@AGENTS.md` + `## Claude Code`); no symlink fallback.\n- Imports \"load at launch\" and do not reduce context, so the token win comes from de-dup into docs\n  and **AGENTS.md must itself be lean.** A grounded estimate puts a complete lean file at ~152\n  lines and ≤ 200 only if the Git/Gerrit section is condensed to agent-actionable rules and defers\n  the full recipe to `CONTRIBUTING.md` (verbatim Gerrit → ~215-230, which misses the target).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `AGENTS.md` exists at repo root and is ≤ 200 lines.\n  - Proving: `test -f AGENTS.md && [ \"$(wc -l < AGENTS.md)\" -le 200 ]`\n- [ ] The Git/Gerrit section is condensed (≤ ~55 lines) and defers the full recipe to\n  `CONTRIBUTING.md`.\n  - Proving: `rg -q 'CONTRIBUTING.md' AGENTS.md`; reviewer confirms the section ≤ 55 lines.\n- [ ] Each already-documented topic is a one-line pointer, not a restated section.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'docs/plan-review-gate.md|docs/mcp-reference.md|docs/ticket-model.md|docs/concurrency.md|docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md|docs/llm-framework.md' AGENTS.md`\n- [ ] Every `docs/…md` path that `AGENTS.md` points at resolves to a real file (no dangling\n  pointer; targets created by S1 are in place by then).\n  - Proving: `for p in $(rg -o 'docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md | sort -u); do test -f \"$p\" || { echo \"MISSING $p\"; exit 1; }; done`\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` is a single `@AGENTS.md` import + optional `## Claude Code` section, ≤ 30 lines.\n  - Proving: `[ \"$(rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md)\" = 1 ] && [ \"$(wc -l < CLAUDE.md)\" -le 30 ]`\n- [ ] `make lint` passes.\n  - Proving: `make lint`","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"AGENTS.md","reason":"new canonical dev guide"},{"path":"CLAUDE.md","reason":"reduce to @AGENTS.md pointer"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"],["parent","81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653"]],"parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","parent_status_uuid":"8a701a8e-a0a6-4b2f-8b3c-a3a171b500a6","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4","ticket_type":"story","title":"Create canonical AGENTS.md (rebar dev guide) + reduce CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md pointer","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["d871c0f8-12bf-429f-b8af-315fc47eac4a","5f7861a5-9ff1-4569-8f14-4c7691f22952","6d9ea785-9e4b-4d1e-9f0a-350fb2aacb1f","b5390584-64f6-4847-98cc-df1a23ada60c","bf7a900f-a909-431f-aaf2-906d7ce08f81","045f68c5-2cc8-4f1c-9b42-d43d0c5add96","378ce9f1-7cfc-406a-9bf7-a2ba76d9c57e","4f2a9d2a-045f-4476-9b30-b0f94a256646","3629d3da-980f-421a-843c-fd314cb5e76e","70e9d634-699d-4c2c-965e-f64d4b232518","45d54393-26ae-4602-af4d-35244eb6254c","d0441675-2624-48cd-92ee-14420c16f35e","97b7dc9e-3b3d-4206-844f-c95f5c113689","f625b7ff-e4be-4a47-9754-ce0560d8eb79","a40c303c-69c9-4f21-880e-aa87153845a6","cec5f840-0b6b-416a-ae27-51d122a6e230","8a701a8e-a0a6-4b2f-8b3c-a3a171b500a6","5f5de3af-73a0-4387-a030-8f7221fbef02"]},"env_id":"","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784346237657362001,"uuid":"3f3f5da8-3f4b-44af-9f9c-617120a3f3c2"}